		<item>
		<title>How to setup bot Persistent Menu?</title>
		<link>https://docs.chatrace.com/kb/persistent-menu/</link>
					<comments>https://docs.chatrace.com/kb/persistent-menu/#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Team]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 14 Feb 2020 09:44:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://docs.chatrace.com/?post_type=kb&#038;p=550</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[The persistent menu allows you to have an always-on user interface element inside your bot conversations. This is an easy way to help people discover]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>The persistent menu allows you to have an always-on user interface element inside your bot conversations. This is an easy way to help people discover and access the core functionality of your bot at any point in the conversation. </p>



<p>The menu is always available to users. This menu should contain the top-level actions that users can use at any time. Having a menu easily communicates the basic capabilities of your chatbot for beginners and returned users.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="673" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-10-1024x673.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2432" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-10-1024x673.png 1024w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-10-300x197.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-10-768x504.png 768w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-10.png 1125w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p></p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Supported Channels</h4>



<p>Currently, the persistent menu is supported on Messenger, Instagram, and Webchat.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Creating the Persistent Menu</h4>



<p>Navigate to Settings > Channels (Messenger, Instagram) > Persistent Menu</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="602" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-11-1024x602.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2433" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-11-1024x602.png 1024w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-11-300x176.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-11-768x452.png 768w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-11.png 1459w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>After clicking the “edit” button on the persistent menu settings, you will get a setup wizard similar to the image below.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="403" src="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-12-1024x403.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2434" srcset="https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-12-1024x403.png 1024w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-12-300x118.png 300w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-12-768x302.png 768w, https://docs.chatrace.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/image-12.png 1461w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p></p>



<p>If you don&#8217;t want your users to send a text message, you can disable the message composer by unchecking the &#8220;<strong>Allow Keyboard Input</strong>&#8220;. </p>



<p></p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading"></h4>
]]></content:encoded>
					
